    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1435381446?book_show_action=true">Nov 06, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Matt" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Matt" rel="nofollow" href="/user/show/5861644-matt">Matt</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1435381446" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12643246208133061785">I had the pleasure of interviewing Michael Swanwick for a local convention a few months ago, having only read his brilliant comedy Chasing The Phoenix. Today, I finished his award-winning Stations Of The Tide, a book just as wonderful but in almost opposite directions. Sci-fi elements aside, this is a noir story. A man known only as the beaurocrat (evoking the Pinkerton Agent of classic noir stories) is investigating a criminal in a corrupt little world on the brink of environmental cataclysm. H</span>
  <span id="freeText12643246208133061785" style="display:none">I had the pleasure of interviewing Michael Swanwick for a local convention a few months ago, having only read his brilliant comedy Chasing The Phoenix. Today, I finished his award-winning Stations Of The Tide, a book just as wonderful but in almost opposite directions. Sci-fi elements aside, this is a noir story. A man known only as the beaurocrat (evoking the Pinkerton Agent of classic noir stories) is investigating a criminal in a corrupt little world on the brink of environmental cataclysm. His work exposes him to hallucinogens, a cast of mysterious locals, and tantric sex with a classic femme fatale. His experiences with the advanced technology and ancient mysticism lead to extended surreal passages, so though the plot of the novel could behard to follow, it was always engaging, pulling the reader along a current. Themes of identity, guilt, transformation, and destiny surface elegantly throughout. This is one of the most original works of science fiction I have read in years.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12643246208133061785" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


